SANScalibration is a Graphical User Interface on top of the LENS Data Reduction 
program for background and transmission files. 

Requirements:
	install the IDL Virtual Machine for your system
	(http://www.ittvis.com/download/download.asp?urlProductCode=13)

To install this application, just run install_SANScalibration. This program will 
copy the necessary folders and the .sav (IDL Virtual Machine executable file) 
to the final location.

> ./install_SANScalibration -d <where to intall the software> 
                                           -n <full name of executable file>

ex: 
> ./install_SANScalibration -d /usr/local/bin/ -n  ~/bin/mySANScalibration

To run the application, launch the executable file you defined
> ~/bin/mySANScalibration

You can get help about how to install this software by doing
> ./install_SANScalibration -h
or send an email to 
bilheuxjm@ornl.gov

